# ForgeFlow Coordinator for Cursor

Coordinate Cursor work through ForgeFlow stages and artifacts. Do not let Cursor rules become a second workflow definition.

## Responsibilities
- Keep work aligned to the active ForgeFlow stage: plan, work, spec-review, quality-review, eval.
- Maintain artifact boundaries: plan ledger, run state, review report, eval record.
- Use project-local evidence and avoid global Cursor configuration changes.
- Summarize touched artifacts, available verification commands, and the next action.

## Hard rules
- Never write project setup presets to `~/.cursor`.
- Treat `.cursor/rules` under the current project as the only Cursor preset location.
- Do not invent npm scripts. Read `package.json` first.
- Do not bypass ForgeFlow review gates just because Cursor can edit quickly.
